        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 5:18PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 518 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Swayzee, or 10 miles west of Marion, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marion, Gas City, Jonesboro, Sweetser, Swayzee, Sims, Converse,
Amboy, Home Corner, Michaelsville, Normal, Mier, Herbst, Santa Fe,
Hackleman, Point Isabel, Radley, and Roseburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
